               <desc type="site-data" xml:lang="en" source="#bibl000284-2">
                  <p>First established by Wuyue Kingdom in 970, prior to Wuyue capitulation to the Northern Song, the Liuhe Pagoda (六和塔) was constructed to store relic and calm the tides of Qiantang River. Built on a riverbank, it also functioned as a lighthouse. The original structure was destroyed completely during a battle in 1121 (Yang, 369). The tower was rebuilt into an tower-style pagoda (louge shi ta 樓閣式塔) in 1153 during the Southern Song Dynasty, and its inner brick tower still exists today. After that, the pagoda experienced several significant modifications. The tower was reconstructed both in 1573 and 1735 (Liang). During the latest restoration in the 1900, the wooden eaves and exterior structures were added to the Southern Song brick structure (Yang, 369).</p> 
                  <p>The Liuhe Pagoda was built on a 0.73-meter tall octagonal brick podium. Tapering upward, the tower is 59.8 meters tall (Wang, 87). Although the tower appears to have thirteen stories, there are only seven floors inside of it. Each floor consists of exterior wooden walls, an ambulatory, brick interior walls, and an inner sanctuary. The brick inner sanctuary imitates timber-frame structures. The size of its corbelled bracket sets strictly follows the standards for grade two modules preserved in the Yingzao fashi (Guo, 76). Inside the ambulatory, a staircase spirals upward. All the doors and shrines are decorated with cusped arches, and Sumeru-style platforms (须弥座) are set below each shrine. The platform is curved with figures including flowers and sacred animals in Chinese tradition, such as qilin (麒麟), suanni (狻猊), and xiezhi (獬豸) (Wang, 89).</p> 
               </desc>  
                  <desc type="site-data" xml:lang="zh-Hans">
                  <p>公元970年，吴越王尚未归顺北宋。为珍藏舍利，镇定江潮，引导往来船只，吴越王在钱塘江畔设立六和塔。原塔于北宋宣和三年（1121）年在方腊起义中损毁。绍兴二十三年（1153），南宋朝廷于原址重建楼阁式塔，其砖质塔身保存至今。之后六和塔多次受损于战乱，几经修缮。塔身在、于万历元年（1573）和雍正十三年（1735）两次重建。光绪二十六年（1900），木檐和木质塔身被加装在了南宋时期遗留的砖质结构上。</p>
                  <p>六和塔的条石塔基呈八边形，高0.73米。塔身高59.8米，向上逐层收缩。虽然外部木檐表面有十三层，但塔身内部只有七个明层可以通行。塔身结构从外而内由木檐、回廊、砖质内墙和小室构成。砖结构采用仿木建筑形式，其斗拱尺寸严格遵循《营造法式》规定的二等材的大小。回廊内设有踏道，环绕塔身向上。塔内的门和龛均装饰有壶门，龛下设有须弥座。须弥座的砖雕刻有各式花卉和麒麟、狻猊、獬豸等中国传统神兽。</p>
               </desc>
